column2: Clear sunny day- very little wind- other conditions normal.
Overcast and sighted many ducks and one 19" bass.  Water pale green.
Cold and windy.  No rain but overcast.
Sunny- windy- beautiful day.  Loon flying over calling out with song!  Ten frogs on a log.
Sunny day- slight breeze.  Many birds.
Cold- clear- sunny weather.  No wind.  Wood ducks present.
beautiful sunny day- observed marsh merrygolds- ducks- turtles on log and many swooping birds
beautiful sunny day- observed many birds- kingfisher among them- loons overhead
beautiful- partly cloudy- sunny day- slight breeze
beautiful crisp sunny day- slight breeze- much bird activity along shoreline- counted eight ducks
windy overcast day- noticed many nesting birds- call of the loon was forceful
Slight breeze- beautiful sunny day- Mother duck with seven ducklings- noticed seven turtles on a log
Breezy north wind- cold clear day- Mother duck still with seven ducklings
Breezy clear day- south wind- some ducks and one eagle
Breezy north wind- sighted geese- various ducks and terns
Cold- clear windy morning. Many birds on shoreline.
cold- clear calm morning. Many birds on the shoreline.
very cold- 40 degrees. sunny- calm morning. Heard wild turkeys in woods.

Clear sky- no wind- northern pike and yellow perch sighted as went to testing location. bottom is silt abou7t 6 to 8 inches deep. There are only 2 or 3 areas of shunenberg lake that have enouth depth to use secci dish and both of these seem to be near natural spring activity. The general depth is less than 6 feet on the average and the wateer is clear down to he silt level at the bottom.  There is a large amount of floating algae apparent. My wife- Bobbie Pearson- swims in the lake almost every day the waqter temp ios above 60 and is complaining that the vegetation is making the water more cloudy this year than in the past. Ron Pearson- assistant; 5685 Snowshoe road Barnes 54873 715-795-2081 for further infl.
loon nest active- fisherman no luck- eagle-

water level is high; we have had 11 inches of rain in last two weeks and lake is up about 10 inches. temp outside is 77 and clear. much of cloudiness of water has moved downstream since Shunenberg is a flowage/seerpage lake. Eagle overhead fishing.  Several 12 t0 14 inch bass sighted at about 8 feet near weed line.
coots- sunny- partly cloudy-rined earlier and thunderstorm
Reading called in by Grace Wisdom.  Water level was 15 feet 8 inches.
